                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-04T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1928—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90. Your 92, October 2, 3 p.m. Department assumes that decision to call meeting
                    on December 5 is based on last paragraph of resolution adopted by Third
                    Committee as quoted on page 236 of Assembly Journal No. 14, September 18. Please
                    report by telegraph any developments which may have taken place in direction of
                    ending deadlock and whether there is greater prospect of an agreement at
                    forthcoming session.</p>
                <p>Department did not receive your despatch No. 584, September 10, until yesterday
                    and the comments you request will be sent as soon as it has had time to study
                    your report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
